agels in water, three or four at a time, cooking for 30 seconds then flipping over with a slotted spoon and cooking for a further 30 seconds. Transfer bagels to paper towels to drain then continue until all bagels have been boiled."},{"content":"Return bagels to prepared trays. In a small bowl, mix together poppy seeds, sesame seeds, fried onions, garlic flakes and 1 tsp salt. Brush each bagel with a little beaten egg then sprinkle with seed mixture."},{"content":"Bake for 12-15 minutes (220°C) until golden brown. Leave to cool slightly on baking trays then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Bagels are a great alternative to sandwiches and these mini ones are more manageable for little hands. Fun to make with their characteristic holes, this is a great recipe to prepare at the weekend then freeze, ready to defrost and toast throughout the week."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 20m","20 pieces"]}